&amp;#x003C;img src=&quot;63.JPG&quot; alt=&quot;63.JPG&quot; title=&quot;63&quot; width=&quot;656&quot; height=&quot;605&quot; style=&quot;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; text-align: center;&quot;/&amp;#x003E;</question><clue></clue><category></category><weighting>100</weighting><fixed>0</fixed><question-type>1</question-type><answers><answer><text>Antivirus scan is disabled under System -&amp;#x003E; Feature visibility</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>None of the inspected protocols are active in this profile.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>The Feature Set for the profile is Flow-based but it must be Proxy-based</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>FortiGate. with less than 2 GB RAM. does not support the Antivirus scan feature.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer></answers></question-record><question-record><question>FortiGate is integrated with FortiAnalyzer and FortiManager. 
When creating a firewall policy, which attribute must an administrator include to enhance functionality and enable log recording on FortiAnalyzer and FortiManager?</question><clue></clue><category></category><weighting>100</weighting><fixed>0</fixed><question-type>1</question-type><answers><answer><text>Universally Unique Identifier</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Policy ID</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Sequence ID</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Log ID</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer></answers></question-record><question-record><question>How does FortiExtender connect to FortiSASE in a site-based, remote internet access method?</question><clue></clue><category></category><weighting>100</weighting><fixed>0</fixed><question-type>1</question-type><answers><answer><text>FortiExtender uses a Virtual Extensible LAN (VXLAN)-over-IPsec connection.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>FortiExtender establishes a secure SSL connection using FortiClient</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>FortiExtender first connects to a FortiGate LAN extension through a secure web gateway (SWG).</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>FortiExtender uses the proxy auto-configuration &amp;#x003C;PAC) file and an explicit web proxy to connect.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer></answers></question-record><question-record><question>What are two features of collector agent advanced mode? (Choose two.) </question><clue></clue><category></category><weighting>100</weighting><fixed>0</fixed><question-type>4</question-type><answers><answer><text>In advanced mode, security profiles can be applied only to user groups, not individual users.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>In advanced mode. FortiGate can be configured as an LDAP client and group filters can be configured on FortiGate.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Advanced mode uses the Windows convention&amp;#x201D;NetBios: Domain\Username.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Advanced mode supports nested or inherited groups.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer></answers><must-select-all>1</must-select-all></question-record><question-record><question>You have configured the below commands on a FortiGate. 
&amp;#x003C;img src=&quot;64.JPG&quot; alt=&quot;64.JPG&quot; title=&quot;64&quot; width=&quot;343&quot; height=&quot;182&quot; style=&quot;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; text-align: center;&quot;/&amp;#x003E;
What would be the impact of this configuration on FortiGate?</question><clue></clue><category></category><weighting>100</weighting><fixed>0</fixed><question-type>1</question-type><answers><answer><text>FortiGate will enable strict RPF on all its interfaces and porti will be exempted from RPF checks.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>FortiGate will enable strict RPF on all its interfaces and porti will be enable for asymmetric routing.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>The global configuration will take precedence and FortiGate will enable strict RPF on all interfaces.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Port1 will be enabled with flexible RPF. and all other interfaces will be enabled for strict RPF</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer></answers></question-record><question-record><question>An administrator wants to create a new static route so the traffic to the subnet 172.20.1.0 is routed through port2 only. What are the two criteria that the administrator can use to achieve this objective? (Choose two.) 
&amp;#x003C;img src=&quot;65.JPG&quot; alt=&quot;65.JPG&quot; title=&quot;65&quot; width=&quot;788&quot; height=&quot;295&quot; style=&quot;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; text-align: center;&quot;/&amp;#x003E;</question><clue></clue><category></category><weighting>100</weighting><fixed>0</fixed><question-type>4</question-type><answers><answer><text>The new static route must have the priority set to 3.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>The new static route must have the metric set to 1.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>The existing static route through port3 must have the distance set to 11.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>The new static route must have the distance set to 9</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer></answers><must-select-all>1</must-select-all></question-record><question-record><question>There are multiple dialup IPsec VPNs configured in aggressive mode on the HQ FortiGate. The  requirement is to connect dial-up users to their respective department VPN tunnels.  Which phase 1 setting you can configure to match the user to the tunnel ?</question><clue></clue><category></category><weighting>100</weighting><fixed>0</fixed><question-type>1</question-type><answers><answer><text>Local Gateway</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Dead Peer Detection</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Peer ID</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>IKE Mode Config</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer></answers></question-record><question-record><question>A network administrator has enabled full SSL inspection and web filtering on FortiGate. When visiting any HTTPS websites, the browser reports certificate warning errors. When visiting HTTP websites, the browser does not report errors. 
What is the reason for the certificate warning errors?</question><clue></clue><category></category><weighting>100</weighting><fixed>0</fixed><question-type>1</question-type><answers><answer><text>The option invalid SSL certificates is set to allow on the SSL/SSH inspection profile.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>The matching firewall policy is set to proxy inspection mode.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>The browser does not trust the certificate used by FortiGate for SSL inspection.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>The certificate used by FortiGate for SSL inspection does not contain the required certificate 
extensions.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer></answers></question-record><question-record><question>You have configured an application control profile, set peer-to-peer traffic to Block under the 
Categories tab. and applied it to the firewall policy. However, your peer-to-peer traffic on known ports is passing through the FortiGate without being blocked. 
What FortiGate settings should you check to resolve this issue? </question><clue></clue><category></category><weighting>100</weighting><fixed>0</fixed><question-type>1</question-type><answers><answer><text>FortiGuard category ratings</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Network Protocol Enforcement</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Replacement Messages for UDP-based Applications</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Application and Filter Overrides</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer></answers></question-record><question-record><question>What are two characteristics of HA cluster heartbeat IP addresses in a FortiGate device? (Choose two.) </question><clue></clue><category></category><weighting>100</weighting><fixed>0</fixed><question-type>4</question-type><answers><answer><text>Heartbeat IP addresses are used to distinguish between cluster members.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>The heartbeat interface of the primary device in the cluster is always assigned IP address 169.254.0.1.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>A change in the heartbeat IP address happens when a FortiGate device joins or leaves the cluster.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Heartbeat interfaces have virtual IP addresses that are manually assigned.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer></answers><must-select-all>1</must-select-all></question-record><question-record><question>Refer to the exhibit. 
Based on the routing table shown in the exhibit, which two statements are true? (Choose two.)
&amp;#x003C;img src=&quot;66.JPG&quot; alt=&quot;66.JPG&quot; title=&quot;66&quot; width=&quot;522&quot; height=&quot;160&quot; style=&quot;display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; text-align: center;&quot;/&amp;#x003E;</question><clue></clue><category></category><weighting>100</weighting><fixed>0</fixed><question-type>4</question-type><answers><answer><text>A packet with the source IP address 10.0.13.10 arriving on port2 is allowed if strict RPF is disabled.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>A packet with the source IP address 10.100.110.10 arriving on port2 is allowed if strict RPF is enabled.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>A packet with the source IP address 10.100.110.10 arriving on port3 is allowed if strict RPF is disabled.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>A packet with the source IP address 10.10.10.10 arriving on port2 is allowed if strict RPF is enabled</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer></answers><must-select-all>1</must-select-all></question-record><question-record><question>FortiGate is operating in NAT mode and has two physical interfaces connected to the LAN and DMZ networks respectively. Which two statements about the requirements of connected physical interfaces on FortiGate are true? (Choose two.) </question><clue></clue><category></category><weighting>100</weighting><fixed>0</fixed><question-type>4</question-type><answers><answer><text>Both interfaces must have DHCP enabled and interfaces set to LAN and DMZ roles assigned.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Both interfaces must have the interface role assigned.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>0</correct><percent-correct>0</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Both interfaces must have directly connected routes on the routing table.</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer><answer><text>Both interfaces must have IP addresses assigned</text><feedback></feedback><correct>1</correct><percent-correct>100</percent-correct><include-in-mc-options>1</include-in-mc-options></answer></answers><must-select-all>1</must-select-all></question-record><question-record><question>A web filter profile configuration and firewall policy configuration are shown. 
